description:
This is a 12 minute workout called 'Competitive Reflections Row' from the channel Aisyah Rafaee.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Beginner fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Competitor and The Meditative Grind vibe.
The The Competitor vibe means Gamified, leaderboard-driven, full-send energy. This is especially good for Those who need to chase a score or beat their own record. The The Meditative Grind vibe means Zone in, lock down, let repetition take over. This is especially good for Those who love a slow burn and rhythmic intensity..
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Celebrate your Hydrow Games journey with Aisyah in this reflective 10-minute Breathe workout. Fresh from competing on the world stage in Paris, Aisyah shares inspiring insights as you work through a ladder structure, building rhythm and speed with bursts of intensity that honor your commitment. Whether you raced in the Hydrow Games or are here to support fellow rowers, this workout will leave you motivated and ready to apply these lessons to all areas of your life. Max rhythm: 26, Format: Climb...
